President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Bruce Hamilton for the position of Member of the Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board. Hamilton has been serving as a Member of the Board since August 2015 and has over 30 years of experience in the nuclear energy field. Prior to his current role, he was the President of Fuelco LLC from 2009 to 2013 and an engineering director at Comanche Peak Nuclear Power Plant from 2003 to 2008. Hamilton also served in the U.S. Navy from 1978 to 2002, retiring as a Captain. He has a background in nuclear operations and holds a B.S. from Texas A&M University, an M.A. from the U.S. Naval Postgraduate School, and a Ph.D. from The Fletcher School of Law & Diplomacy.